01:01.860 --> 01:04.362
He was a very great trial lawyer.

01:05.101 --> 01:07.965
and President of the American Bar Association, etc.

01:08.887 --> 01:09.988
And he became a book collector.

01:11.611 --> 01:16.939
And Dave Randall called on him to sell him some books with a suitcase for him.

01:16.979 --> 01:17.520
He was busy.

01:19.082 --> 01:23.689
So he went into the men's room, Randall did, and was voiding.

01:25.091 --> 01:30.079
When the voice came over the speaker system, Mr. Hogan will now see Mr. Randall.

01:31.696 --> 01:32.517
He was so excited.

01:32.537 --> 01:33.358
This is the 30s.

01:33.378 --> 01:35.199
He couldn't find buyers.

01:35.820 --> 01:51.375
So he runs into Frank Hogan's office, and the first thing that Hogan says to him, Randall, I'm not accustomed to having men walk into my office when my secretary is sitting here with their fly open.

01:52.717 --> 01:56.040
That put Randall into terror.

01:56.060 --> 01:57.421
He began to butt his fly.

01:57.441 --> 01:58.342
He didn't know what to do.

01:59.443 --> 02:00.184
