02:03.631 --> 02:04.892
He said, how much you want for this book?

02:06.374 --> 02:10.820
The guy, Scribner told him, so much.

02:11.841 --> 02:13.363
And he said, I'm not going to pay that.

02:13.383 --> 02:14.204
I'll pay so-and-so.

02:16.927 --> 02:19.069
And Randall says, OK, you're going to have for so-and-so.

02:19.430 --> 02:20.811
And they began their relationship.

02:22.453 --> 02:27.960
So when they became friends, Hogan said that he'd like him to see

02:28.700 --> 02:39.135
a Mark, a Huckleberry Finn manuscript that he had given to Georgetown, where he'd gone to school, the law school, nights.

02:40.718 --> 02:43.001
So he takes Dave Randall, Dave, I wanted to see it.

02:44.023 --> 02:57.222
They go over to the library, and he asked, Hogan asked the librarian where the manuscript is, and she says it's in the basement, section C, shelf four, gives him all the descriptions.

02:57.877 --> 03:09.616
So he and Randall go down, and they're lying on the floor, wrapped with a piece of twine, gathering dust, is this Huckleberry Finn manuscript.

03:11.479 --> 03:16.326
Whereupon Hogan turns to Randall and he says, Dave, that settles it.

03:16.346 --> 03:18.269
