So how does it, what happens?

25:41.287 --> 25:45.873
I dropped in on a Friday afternoon and I said, what have you got for me?

25:45.893 --> 25:46.614
He says, look around.

25:46.634 --> 25:48.035
I looked around.

25:48.055 --> 25:52.120
He says, you know, Abel, you remind me of Blue Silver.

25:53.302 --> 25:54.163
And I said, why?

25:55.104 --> 25:57.908
He says, you have the same nose for books that he did.

25:58.488 --> 25:59.389
I wish that were true.

25:59.970 --> 26:01.512
I wish that what he said

26:02.015 --> 26:07.941
It had been true, because Silver had the most magnificent judgment when it came to books.

26:09.022 --> 26:14.767
As profane a man as he was, when he came to books, he was in a class by himself.

26:15.768 --> 26:21.474
But that was Fleming's way of flattering me, that I would pick the important books.

26:23.016 --> 26:27.320
And he never offered me a book, except the text, which I will show you later.

26:27.420 --> 26:28.881
Fleming never offered you a book.

26:28.901 --> 26:31.684
You know, he never called up and said, Abel, I've got this book.

26:32.204 --> 26:32.985
Are you interested?"

26:33.666 --> 26:35.228
He would say, well look around, see what you want.

26:36.109 --> 26:38.072
Did he call you if he hadn't heard from you in a while?

26:38.452 --> 26:39.093
No, never.

